## Input Feature Reference

| Feature           | Type   | Valid Values                                    | Example       |
|-------------------|--------|-------------------------------------------------|---------------|
| `tenure`          | int    | 1–72 (months with the company)                  | `12`          |
| `monthly_charges` | float  | 20.0–120.0 (monthly bill in $)                  | `70.5`        |
| `total_charges`   | float  | 100.0–8000.0 (total amount billed in $)         | `840.0`       |
| `contract`        | string | `"Month-to-month"`, `"One year"`, `"Two year"`  | `"One year"`  |
| `internet_service`| string | `"DSL"`, `"Fiber optic"`, `"No"`                | `"DSL"`       |
| `gender`          | string | `"Male"`, `"Female"`                            | `"Female"`    |

---

## Verified Test Results

Both prediction paths were tested and confirmed working:

| Scenario            | Input Summary                                  | Prediction | Label     |
|---------------------|------------------------------------------------|------------|-----------|
| High-risk customer  | tenure=2, month-to-month, fiber, $110/mo       | `1`        | Churn     |
| Low-risk customer   | tenure=5, month-to-month, fiber, $95/mo        | `0`        | No Churn  |

Model accuracy on test set: **68.5%** (expected for synthetic data — real-world datasets typically yield higher accuracy).
